lg.l:
The double circle is drawn with Kashmiri saffron “Saffron” is tentatively inserted. The source texts
                read only “Kashmiri” (kāśmira;
                  kha che yi).

To summon, Skt. reads “to praise”
                  (praśastam).  mounted on a
              goat;

note.p:
In Mahāyāna doctrine, bodhicitta refers to the aspiration
                  for awakening, in both its relative and absolute aspects. In tantric literature,
                  it frequently refers to semen.
